ypic index R to assess the importance of clonal reproduction, at least\nwhen the impact of selfing on Fis can be neglected. The results also emphasize\nthe need to revise our appraisal of the extent of clonality and its influence\non the dynamics, connectivity and evolutionary trajectory of partial asexuals\nin general, including in seagrass meadows, to develop the most accurate\nmanagement strategies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Feb 2019 21:48:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 1 Jul 2019 19:16:13 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 6 Sep 2019 15:22:28 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 25 Oct 2019 16:08:29 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Sun, 3 Nov 2019 11:33:59 GMT"},{"version":"v6","created":"Tue, 5 Nov 2019 22:09:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-11-07"}
